;WFW3.11 Installation Information
;================================

:w_underwin "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 You are attempting to run Setup from within
 Windows. You need to quit Windows and then
 run Setup from the MS-DOS command prompt.

 Or you can run the Windows version of Setup
 by clicking the Windows Setup icon in the
 Main group in Program Manager

 To quit Setup, select ~QUIT~

                 [ QUIT ]
::

:w_no386 "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Microsoft Windows for Workgroups 3.11 requires
 an Intel 80386 or higher CPU in your system.

 Setup cannot continue. To quit Setup, select ~QUIT~

                 [ QUIT ]
::

:welcome "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Welcome to Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup.

 When Setup is complete, you will be able to use
 Microsoft Windows for Workgroups 3.11 on your computer.

 To set up Windows for Workgroups 3.11 now, select ~NEXT~
 To quit without setting up, select ~QUIT~

                  [ NEXT ]  [ QUIT ]                 
::

:w_partitionhdd "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Setup needs to configure the unallocated space on your
 hard disk to prepare it for use with Windows.

 To have Setup configure the space on your hard disk for
 you, choose the ~PARTITION HARD DISK~ option.

           [ PARTITION HARD DISK ]  [ QUIT ]
::

:w_partcomp "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Partitioning has been completed.
 
 Setup will restart you computer in ~#?~ Seconds.
 
 Please make sure the Windows for Workgroups 3.11
 installation media remains in your disk drive.


                  [ RESTART ]
::

:w_formathdd "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Hard disk drive C is not formatted. Windows for Workgroups 3.11
 cannot use unformatted drives.
 
 Setup can format this drive, or you can quit Setup and format
 the drive yourself.

 To have Setup format hard disk drive C, select ~FORMAT~

                    [ FORMAT ]  [ QUIT ]
::

:w_nohd "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Setup cannot configure your hard disk drive.

 There was an unknown error with you hard disk drive
 and Setup cannot continue.

 Setup will not exit.

                   [ QUIT ]
::

:w_nord "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Setup cannot create a RAM drive or Temporary Folder
 for the Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup.

 Setup cannot continue and will now exit.

                   [ QUIT ]
::

:w_path "Set Insallation Directory" [x]

 Windows for Workgroups 3.11 will be set up in the following
 directory.

 [$ ins_path,80                                             ]

 To set up Windows for Workgroups 3.11 in this directory,
 select ~CONTINUE~.

 To set up Windows for Workgroups 3.11 in a different directory,
 use the ~BACKSPACE~ key to delete characters, and then type
 a new directory.

                       [ CONTINUE ]
::

:w_dossetcomp "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 This portion of Setup has completed successfully.

 Setup will restart your computer in ~#?~ Seconds.

 Select ~RESTART~ to restart your computer now.
 When your computer restarts, Setup will continue.

                  [ RESTART ]
::

