:w_overwrite "Existing Installation Found" [x]

 Setup has found an existing installation of Microsoft Windows
 on your hard disk in the path shown below.

    ~%ins_path%~


 - To overwrite your existing installation and use this directory
   select ~OVERWRITE~.

 - To change to a different directory select ~CHANGE~.

                   [ OVERWRITE ] [ CHANGE ]
::

:w_sysnt "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Setup has detected Windows NT Boot Files on your system.

  - To attempt to create a Dual-Boot with NT, Select ~CONTINUE~.

  - To overwrite the NT bootsector, select ~OVERWRITE~.
      NOTE: Windows NT will no longer be bootable with this option.
  
  - to exit setup without making any changes select ~QUIT~

            [ CONTINUE ] [ OVERWRITE ] [ QUIT ]
::

:w_sysdos "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Setup has found MS-DOS Boot Files on your system. Setup will 
 upgrade these files automatically. 
 
  - If you do not want to upgrade MS-DOS, select ~QUIT~ to exit 
    without making any changes.

                  [ CONTINUE ] [ QUIT ]
::


:w_partfail "Windows for Workgroups 3.11 Setup" [x]

 Setup has found a Non-DOS partition on your system.

 Windows for Workgroups 3.11 requires the first partition
 to be a primary DOS partition for installation.

 Would you like Setup to format partition ~1~ as a Primary
 DOS partition? 

           [ FORMAT PARTITION ]  [ QUIT ]
::